thread.title: Treasurys Strengthen Following Soft Eurozone Inflation Data

author: Sam Goldfarb
title: Treasurys Strengthen Following Soft Eurozone Inflation Data

organizations.name: treasurys strengthen following soft eurozone inflation data

text:
U.S. government bond prices edged higher Thursday as traders reacted to softer-than-expected eurozone inflation data.
The yield on the benchmark 10-year U.S. Treasury note settled at 2.946%, compared with 2.964% Wednesday.
Yields, which fall when bond prices rise, slid after a report showed eurozone inflation in April was 0.7% excluding energy,...
